  "text": "Cats weighing 1.5-3.0 kg were anesthetized with sodium pentobarbital, [CITATION_1] mg/kg i.p. The hearts were rapidly removed and immersed in Tyrode's solution of the following composition in mM: NaCl, 135.4; KC1, 5.4; NaH2PO4, 1.8; CaCl2, 2.7; MgCl2, 0.5; NaHCO3, 18; and dextrose, 5.5. Solutions were bubbled with 95% 02-5% CO2. Bath temperature was 32+ 1°C and bath flow rate 15 ml/min.",
